# weir.env.example — secrets/env template for the weir systemd unit.
#
# Copy to /etc/weir/weir.env, fill in real values, and lock it down:
#
#   sudo install -m0640 -o root -g weir weir.env.example /etc/weir/weir.env
#   sudo $EDITOR /etc/weir/weir.env
#
# Mode 0640 root:weir keeps it readable by the daemon but not world-readable.
# (0600 root:root also works if you don't mind root-only reads; the unit reads
# it as root before dropping to User=weir.) DO NOT commit a filled-in copy with
# real secrets — keep credentials out of version control.
#
# These are consumed via EnvironmentFile= in weir.service. WEIR_* env vars
# override the TOML file, so anything set here wins over /etc/weir/weir.toml.
# Every line is `KEY=value` (no `export`, no quotes needed by systemd).
#
# Why secrets live HERE and not in weir.toml:
#   - WEIR_SINK_BEARER_TOKEN is env-ONLY by design — it is never read from the
#     TOML file or a CLI flag (it would otherwise land in config on disk, image
#     layers, and `cat`-able files).
#   - A credential-bearing WEIR_SINK_URL belongs in env so the password is not
#     written to disk (the TOML has no on-disk redaction) and stays out of the
#     process argv visible to `ps aux`.
# Verified against crates/weir-server/src/config/env.rs (WEIR_SINK_URL) and
# crates/weir-server/src/main.rs (WEIR_SINK_BEARER_TOKEN).

# ── HTTP sink ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Endpoint that receives one POST per record (or one NDJSON POST per batch).
# WEIR_SINK_URL=https://ingest.internal.example.com/weir
#
# Sent as `Authorization: Bearer <token>` on every HTTP-sink request.
# WEIR_SINK_BEARER_TOKEN=replace-with-real-token

# ── SQL sinks (mysql / postgres) ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# The connection URL carries credentials — set it HERE, never in the TOML.
# WEIR_SINK_URL=postgres://weir:CHANGE_ME@db.internal:5432/weir?sslmode=require
# WEIR_SINK_URL=mysql://weir:CHANGE_ME@db.internal:3306/weir

# ── Optional non-secret overrides ────────────────────────────────────────────
# Any WEIR_* knob can be set here too (handy for per-host tweaks without editing
# the shared TOML). Example:
# WEIR_LOG_LEVEL=info
